title: New data on cross-sections of deuteron induced nuclear reactions on gold up to 50 MeV and comparison of production routes of medically relevant Au and Hg radioisotopes

x4freetext: Natural gold foil, thickness: 25 microns as backing of
Ga-Ni (70-30%) electroplated samples
One stack containing 22 Ga-Ni targets on Au backing
interleaved with Al (98 um and 49.6 um) and
Ni (23.9 um) monitor/degrader foils. The stack was
irradiated in Faraday cup like target holder.
The beam current was kept constant, 100 nA (+-5%).
Irradiation time: 60 min.
The activities of the produced radionuclides were
measured nondestructively without chemical separation.
The energy degradation as a function of depth in the
stack was calculated from the input energy and target
thicknesses.
Chapter 4
Decay data were taken from NuDat2.6 database.
The uncertainty of the primary beam energy
was estimated as (+-0.2 MeV) which increased due to
straggling effect continuously in each foil through the
stack.
Typical total uncertainty is between 10-12%.
number of bombarding particles(5%)
surface density of target atoms(5%)
detector efficiency (5%)
nuclear decay and branching data(5%)
statistical and peak fitting (2-8%)
Integral yields were calculated from the
fitted experimental cross sections.
